<v Speaker 2>Aser.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:06.960
<v Speaker 1>Aser.

00:00:06.960 --> 00:00:11.520
<v Speaker 1>We said that for the informal positive command we have a shortcut.

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:14.960
<v Speaker 1>We find the U version of the verb, Asis.

00:00:14.860 --> 00:00:16.779
<v Speaker 1>and we take away the yes.

00:00:16.779 --> 00:00:17.900
<v Speaker 1>Asi.

00:00:17.900 --> 00:00:20.779
<v Speaker 1>But with ASER we have an irregularity.

00:00:20.779 --> 00:00:23.260
<v Speaker 1>The informal command from ASER is as

00:00:23.920 --> 00:00:25.840
<v Speaker 1>H A Z.

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:29.040
<v Speaker 1>So in most of Spain you will hear as.

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:29.600
<v Speaker 1>As.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:31.200
<v Speaker 1>So if you want to say do it

00:00:32.540 --> 00:00:33.420
<v Speaker 2>Aslo.

00:00:33.420 --> 00:00:34.300
<v Speaker 1>Aslo.

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:35.100
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:42.940
<v Speaker 1>Another use of the mood tense is to turn words like where into wherever.

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:43.900
<v Speaker 1>What was where

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:46.420
<v Speaker 2>Donde.

00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:47.380
<v Speaker 1>Donde.

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:51.780
<v Speaker 1>So of course we can't use the mood tense with donde because it's not a verb.

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.660
<v Speaker 1>How would you say where you want?

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:57.140
<v Speaker 1>Where you want speaking informally

00:00:58.800 --> 00:01:00.160
<v Speaker 2>Donde quieres.

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:01.680
<v Speaker 1>Donde quieres.

00:01:01.680 --> 00:01:02.400
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:10.240
<v Speaker 1>Now if we want to say wherever you want, then to get wherever, actually we can change the verb.

00:01:09.939 --> 00:01:16.500
<v Speaker 1>to the mood tense and that changes the feeling of where and then where turns into wherever.

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:20.420
<v Speaker 1>So if you want to say wherever you want, still informally

00:01:21.900 --> 00:01:23.500
<v Speaker 1>Donte chieras.

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:27.100
<v Speaker 1>I want to hear where load I and the e in chieras.

00:01:27.100 --> 00:01:29.020
<v Speaker 2>Donte chieras.

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:29.420
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:01:29.420 --> 00:01:30.780
<v Speaker 1>Donde chieras.

00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:33.180
<v Speaker 1>So do it wherever you want.

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:36.780
<v Speaker 2>Aslo Donde quieras.

00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:37.580
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:01:37.580 --> 00:01:40.300
<v Speaker 1>Aslo donde quieras.

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:42.700
<v Speaker 1>What was you like it?

00:01:42.700 --> 00:01:45.979
<v Speaker 1>Still informally you like it.

00:01:47.020 --> 00:01:48.140
<v Speaker 2>Te gusta.

00:01:48.140 --> 00:01:49.260
<v Speaker 1>Te gusta.

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:52.460
<v Speaker 1>How would you say do it how you like to do it?

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:54.220
<v Speaker 1>So do it how you like.

00:01:54.220 --> 00:01:56.380
<v Speaker 1>What was the word for how?

00:01:56.700 --> 00:01:57.820
<v Speaker 1>How are you called?

00:01:57.820 --> 00:01:59.420
<v Speaker 1>What's your name?

00:01:59.759 --> 00:02:00.560
<v Speaker 1>Como.

00:02:00.560 --> 00:02:01.200
<v Speaker 1>Como.

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:01.600
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:03.840
<v Speaker 1>So do it how it pleases you.

00:02:03.840 --> 00:02:06.560
<v Speaker 1>Do it how you like.

